<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-06-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 371.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Langston</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port-au-Prince,
                                    Hayti</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-06-16"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 16, 1885</date>.
                            (Received June 30.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 746.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise you that this
                        Government, on the 29th May last, paid in drafts on New York and Europe,
                        duly indorsed by the secretary of state of finances, the respective sums
                        awarded to American citizens by the Americo-Haytian mixed commission, as
                        reported in my dispatch No. 740, less 10 per cent, discount, as agreed,
                        which sums aggregated $5,130, and which have been apportioned and paid as
                        follows: <table cols="2" rows="5">
                            <row>
                                <cell>Mr. C. W. Mossell</cell>
                                <cell role="num">$2,250</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Mr. E. V. Garrido</cell>
                                <cell role="num">765</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Messrs. Bertram Brothers</cell>
                                <cell role="num">990</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Mrs. Maria Hamilton</cell>
                                <cell role="num">495</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Mrs. Isabella Fournier</cell>
                                <cell role="num">630</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table></p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JOHN MERCER LANGSTON.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>